---
---

<section class="section-rule py-16 sm:py-20 px-6 fade-in">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The Principal</p>
    <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl sm:text-4xl leading-tight mb-2">Platte F. Clark</h2>
    <p class="text-xs tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-navy-muted mb-12">
      Principal &middot; Straw Dogs LLC &middot; WGA Member
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-10 lg:gap-14">
      <!-- Photo + Podcast Callout -->
      <div class="md:col-span-1 space-y-8">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/platte-headshot.jpg"
            alt="Platte F. Clark"
            class="w-full aspect-[3/4] object-cover border border-rule"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption class="text-xs italic text-navy-muted mt-2">
            <span class="not-italic font-medium">Premiere</span> &middot; The Best Christmas Pageant Ever
            <br/>Lionsgate, 2024
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <div class="border-t border-rule-strong pt-5">
          <p class="text-xs tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-gold mb-2">
            On the Air &middot; Co-Hosted with Jeff Stutz
          </p>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-2">The Author Unknown Podcast</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-navy-soft leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The science and psychology of why some stories create change&mdash;conversations
            with neuroscientists, AI researchers, behaviorists, and master storytellers on
            the mechanics of belief.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://authorunknown.fm"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-xs tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-gold hover:text-navy transition-colors"
          >
            authorunknown.fm &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bio -->
      <div class="md:col-span-2 space-y-4 text-navy-soft leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Platte F. Clark is the principal of Straw Dogs LLC. He is the credited writer on the
          2024 Lionsgate feature <em>The Best Christmas Pageant Ever</em> (92% Critics, 97%
          Audiences), the novelist behind the <em>Bad Unicorn</em> trilogy at Aladdin / Simon &amp;
          Schuster (250,000+ copies), and the ghostwriter behind nearly thirty nonfiction titles
          for executives, founders, and category-defining experts&mdash;including multiple
          FranklinCovey co-authorship credits with the firm's senior leadership.
        </p>
        <p>
          His work outside the page shapes what his work on the page does. Before ghostwriting
          full-time, Clark built behavioral curriculum for FranklinCovey, CrucialLearning, and
          ZengerFolkman, and served as Chief Learning Officer at a partner company with Tony
          Robbins focused on B-to-B training. That instructional-design background is the engine
          under the architecture: he writes books that change how the reader behaves after they
          close the cover.
        </p>
        <p>
          Clark is currently authoring <em>Author Unknown: Why Some Stories Change People and Most
          Don't</em> (forthcoming, Grey + Miller Agency), a working theory of narrative as
          behavior-change technology.
        </p>
        <p>
          He is a WGA member, holds a B.S. in Philosophy (cum laude&mdash;the BS unintentional)
          and an M.S. in English / Instructional Technology, and lives in American Fork, Utah.
        </p>

        <div class="pt-2">
          <a
            href="https://platteclark.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-xs tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-gold hover:text-navy transition-colors"
          >
            platteclark.com &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
